in this lesson we are creating different pages for different url 




When is the useEffect is called?
useEffect is called after every times the component render
this is the definition of useEffect 
dependency array changes the behaviour of the useEffect

// useeffect  
// if no dependency array ==> useEffect is called on every render 

useEffect(()=>{
    console.log("useEffect called")
})

// if dependency array is empty =[] => useEffect is called on initial render (just once )

import {useState,useEffect} from "react"

const Header=() => {
useEffect(()=>{
    console.log("useEffect called");
},[]);
}


// it will only be called if dependency changes
// if dependency array is [btnNameReact] =>called everytime btnNameReact is updates 

useEffect(()=>{
    console.log("useEffect called");
},[btnNameReact])

// never create useState outside the component
// create it at the start of the component
// never create usestate inside the if-else 

// state variable need to be created at the higher level of the component
//never create the usestate ,useEffect inside the if -else 


