// react application are single page application as every thing is component in react
//you have to navigate through the page your browser will not load ,this is known as single page application
Reactrouter.com/en/main
just the components get interchanged at the client side routing 
// the browser will not the entire page 

There are two routing in web application 
1)Client Side routing
2)Server side routing 



when we are moving to the about us and contact page we are losing the header and footer 
i want to keep my header intact 
Now we see children route inside the route

There are two types of routing in web apps
a)Client Side ROUTING B)Server side Routing 


if i click on the anchor tag /about ,it reloads the whole page ,it sends the networks call to the about.html
fetches that html  and renders that  to the web page 

This is server side routing 

You make the networks call and about.html is coming from the server

1)Client Side Routing  React 

All the components are loaded to the app
when i loaded the app for the first time ,it already has the code for about ,it will just load that componet 
i am not fetching the new page 
2)Server side Routing-you make the network call and page is coming from the server

index.html 
about.html 
contact.html 

if i click on the anchor tag  ./about it reload the whole page ,it sends the  network call to the about.hml 
fetches  that html  and render  that  web page  
we are not making any network call 
all the components are loaded  in our side 

Why react is single page application ?

one page  just components is getting interchanged via client side routing 
